This paper is about machine learning-based hyperspectral image analysis, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper discusses various ML algorithms and their applications, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for analyzing hyperspectral images, which makes cs.IR a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for hyperspectral image analysis, which makes cs.AI another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses deep learning (DL) techniques, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
